The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, July 6: The aviation turbine fuel (ATF) futures contract will be launched on the Multi Commodity Exchange (MCX) on Monday, a top exchange official said. ATF futures is expected to help airline companies as they can use them to hedge their price risk in the commodity and safeguard themselves from the extreme volatility of international prices, the MCX official said.                            
	 New Delhi, July 6: A six-member World Bank team will be here this month to hold discussions with the Indian Railways about funds for the eastern freight corridor project. The Indian Railways, which has approached the World Bank for funding the Rs 12,000-crore project, will present a detailed report of the plan to the visiting team.                            
	 New Delhi, July 6: The UK retail major Marks amp; Spencer (M amp;S) plans to exit from its six-year-old franchisee deal with Planet Retail as part of its effort to focus on the joint venture with Reliance Retail.                            
	 New Delhi, July 6: PFC Consulting will form a joint venture (JV) with an international company next month to provide technical expertise to power utilities. The JV with the international consultancy firm is expected in a months time, a source said.                            
	 Calcutta, July 6: ITCs non-cigarette business contributed nearly 52.4 per cent to the companys net turnover. In a report of ITC directors for the year ended March 31, 2008, it said the company was uniquely positioned to tap emerging opportunities in the fmcg sector.                                                                                                                         
